# Thundercaller
Bound to the Land		KEY:Thundercaller ~ Bound to the Land	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.BardClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.BardFascinate																																																													DESC:A thundercaller gains a bonus equal to 1/2 her level on Handle Animal, Knowledge (nature), and Survival checks. This ability replaces bardic knowledge.																																																																																																																																																																											BONUS:SKILL|Handle Animal,Knowledge (Nature),Survival|ceil(BardLVL/2)			SOURCEPAGE:p.11
Thunder Call		KEY:Thundercaller ~ Thunder Call		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.BardClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Supernatural.BardInspireCompetence																																																												DESC:At 3rd level, the thundercaller can use her performance to unleash a deafening peal of thunder. This allows the thundercaller to spend a round of performance to create an effect similar to the spell sound burst (having the same range and area and allowing the same saving throw). At 7th level, the sonic damage that is dealt by this blast of sound increases to 3d8. This damage further increases to 5d8 at 11th level, 7d8 at 15th level, and 9d8 at 19th level. This performance replaces inspire competence.																																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.11
Incite Rage			KEY:Thundercaller ~ Incite Rage		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.BardClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Supernatural.BardSuggestion.BardMassSuggestion																																																										DESC:At 6th level, a Thundercaller can induce a furious rage in one creature within 30 feet. This effect functions as a rage spell that lasts as long as the target can hear the bard's performance; however, unwilling creatures can be affected if they fail a Will save DC %1 (DC 10 + 1/2 the bard's level + the bard's Cha modifier). Success renders the target immune to this power for 24 hours. The bard cannot target himself with this ability. If the target has the rage class feature, it can instead immediately rage and stay in this rage without consuming rounds of rage per day as long as the bard continues performing. This mind-affecting effect requires audible components. This performance replaces suggestion.|10+CHA+(BardLVL/2)																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.11
Call Lightning		KEY:Thundercaller ~ Call Lightning		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.BardClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Supernatural.BardDirgeOfDoom																																																													DESC:At 8th level, the thundercaller can use her performance to summon bolts of lightning, as per the spell call lightning. The lightning storm lasts for as long as she continues her performance, calling down one bolt of lightning per round. The damage of these lightning bolts can be increased in stormy areas or can be limited as call lightning describes. This performance replaces dirge of doom.																																																																																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.11
Call Lightning Storm	KEY:Thundercaller ~ Call Lightning Storm	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.BardClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Supernatural.BardFrighteningTune																																																												DESC:At 14th level, the thundercaller can use her performance to summon bolts of lightning, as per the spell call lightning storm. The lightning storm lasts for as long as she continues her performance, calling down one bolt of lightning per round. The damage of these lightning bolts can be increased in stormy areas or can be limited as call lightning describes. This performance replaces frightening tune.																																																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.11

